# ============================================================================
# FRONTEND PRODUCTION ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES (.env.production)
# ============================================================================
# 
# This file contains environment-specific configuration for the production
# build of your React application on Vercel.
# 
# IMPORTANT SECURITY NOTES:
# ✓ This file IS committed to git (it's safe - no secrets here)
# ✓ Only VITE_* variables are exposed to browser (prefixed with VITE_)
# ✗ Never put passwords, API keys, or secrets in this file
# ✗ Those should be set in Vercel project settings, not here
#
# File is used by:
# - Vite during build: npm run build
# - Variables available in frontend code: import.meta.env.VITE_*
#
# How to set in Vercel:
# 1. Go to Vercel Dashboard
# 2. Select your project
# 3. Settings → Environment Variables
# 4. Add each variable below
# 5. It will be available in production
#
# ============================================================================

# SUPABASE CONFIGURATION
